formThreeBId.notesToCertificate:
1.	Guidelines of the ICAI restrict any of its member to issue any certificate wherein amounts includes any estimations. However considering the requirement of the RERA this certificate is issued for better compliance of the Act. Figures mentioned in the estimated column are relied upon as by any other expert ? E.g Engineer or the amounts provide by mgmt.
2.	The amount of cost stated above includes audited figures upto 31-3-19 while cost incurred from 01-4-19 to 31-07-2020 are unaudited figures. 
3.	It has been observed that there is a variance in opening balance of escrow account due to an error during any of  the previous quarters. This error has been rectified by showing withdrawal during the reporting quarter. The actual withdrawal during the reporting quarter amounts to Rs 6426350/- which corroborates with the bank statement produced before us.
4.	From 3A, annexure has been reproduced by client. In respect to encumbrance status and agreement for sale is concerned, we are neither technically qualified nor legally entitled to certify such change or status. We are Chartered Accountants and entitled to certify financial data as per book of account. We are neither technically qualified to check architect?s nor engineer?s work, whether it seems coherence with expenditure incurred. We refrain from certifying any variance in data reported in form 1 or form 2, due to any error which doesn't corroborate with the certificates produced by the Architect or Engineer respectively.
